<h3>Converting Dose Equivalent</h3>
<p>Because a rem represents a fairly large dose of radiation, dose is best
expressed as a millirem, or 1/1000 of a rem. The same is true of sieverts. =
Dose
is expressed in millisieverts (mSv). Because 1&nbsp;mrem equals 0.01&nbsp;m=
Sv,
converting from millirem to millisieverts is simply a matter of moving the
decimal point two places to the left. For example, 267&nbsp;mrem equals 2.6=
7&nbsp;mSv.
</p>
